story.title: Saudi Aramco restores oil output earlier than expected - sources
story.summary: SAUDI-ARAMCO/ (URGENT, PIX):Saudi Aramco restores oil output earlier than expected - sources

xmlText.p: Saudi Aramco restores oil output earlier than expected - sources

DUBAI, Sept 25 (Reuters) - Saudi Arabia has restored its oil production capacity to 11.3 million barrels per day after Sept. 14 attacks on oil facilities, three sources briefed on Saudi Aramco's operations told Reuters.
Crude output from the Khurais field is now at 1.3 million bpd and the Abqaiq field is currently at about 4.9 million bpd, the sources said. (Reporting by Rania el Gamal; Editing by Louise Heavnes)
